text.section:
An employee organization may not:
interfere with, restrain, or coerce any employee in the employee's exercise of a right under this subtitle;
cause or attempt to cause the Montgomery Commission to discriminate against an employee in the employee's exercise of a right under this subtitle;
coerce, discipline, fine, or attempt to coerce a member of an employee organization as punishment or reprisal;
coerce, discipline, fine, or attempt to coerce a member of an employee organization to impede the member's work performance;
refuse to negotiate in good faith with the Montgomery Commission as required by this subtitle; or
fail or refuse to cooperate in impasse procedures and impasse decisions as required by this subtitle.
